@node "Introduction"
                      *   * *** ***
                      *   * *   * *
                       * *  *** ***
                       * *  *   **
                        *   *** * *  VERSIONER v2.x

                         ®Ā1995-97 Javier Morata



FreeWare !!

How many times you have to copy libs of a program into the LIBS directory
with this question: What library version I have ? or I need to change this
version ? or It's a new version ?
I don't know you think about this, but I have 5 Meg of libraries and if I have
to do the version of them to know it, I will become fool !!
For this question I created VERsioner, for help us in this task.

@{b}NOTE
~~~~@{ub}
Many INSTALER« scripts don't ask for libraries and only it copy his libraries
and devices directly.
Check before using INSTALER« !! You can lose your newest libraries !!
@endnode

@node "Function"
VERsioner is a program command that adds the versi¾n string of a file into the
comment of same file in automatic way and recursive.
It's optimized to be used with WorkBench 3.x system.
It can be used with DOpus 4.x or later.
@endnode

@node "Requirements"
KickStart 2.04+
WorkBench 2.04+
@{b}An enough RAM memory for load all file names
@endnode

@node "Install"

If you select @{"Install" system "copy versioner c: clone quiet"} the button
will install @{b}VERsioner@{ub} into your C: directory !

@{b}Version to Install:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}
Versioner v2.1b --- ® Javier Morata 1997
(Release 21-Oct)
@endnode

@node "Synopsis"
CLI> @{b}VERsioner -/S DIR_NAME/M PATTERN/M
@endnode

@node "Inputs"
CLI> @{b}VERsioner -/S DIR_NAME/M PATTERN/M@{ub}

-/S            Check for input data

DIR_NAME/M     Name of directory (recursive)
               Name of file

PATTERN/M      Pattern of files
               for file = #?
@endnode

@node "Example"
CLI> VERsioner - dh0:devs #?.device
CLI> VERsioner "ram disk:clipboards" #?~(#?.info|#?.lha)
CLI> VERsioner - "Space Ace:" ~(#?magic#?)
@endnode

@node "Use with DOpus"
@{b}Make a button as...@{ub}

c:versioner {f} {RsPattern:~(#?.info)}

... with options:

"All files"
"Output window"
"Run asynchronously"
@endnode

@node "Danger"
If you make a version of your partition take care because list of all files
in your partition could cause "RAM: is full". Don't worry !
Delete T:VERSIONER for free all memory if VERsioner doesn't make it.
@endnode

@node "History"
v1.0      VERsioner as DOpus button

v1.2      Due of a bug in DOpus recursive command, I make the script

v1.6      Recursive mode installed

v1.8      VERsioner only for files, not directories

v2.0      C program

v2.1      First public version

v2.1a     Update change

v2.1b     Only version of file is read
@endnode

